==Demographics==
As of the [[census]] of 2020, there were 9,992 people in 3,259 households residing in the city. The [[population density]] was {{convert|5,016.1|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|1}}. The racial makeup of the city was 81.4% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 4.0% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.8% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 8.4% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.9% [[Race (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], and 3.6% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 5.57% of the population.

There were 3,259 households. The average household size was 2.93.

25.2% of residents were under the age of 18, and 11.8% were 65 years of age or older. The gender makeup of the city was 49% male and 51% female.<ref>{{Cite web |title=QuickFacts: Bull Mountain CDP, Oregon |url=https://www.census.gov/quickfacts/bullmountaincdporegon |access-date=3 September 2023 |website=U.S. Census Bureau}}</ref>

